An Act to authorize the mayor of the city of Haverhill to submit special legislation to increase
the membership of the board of health from three members to five members.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding section 26 of chapter 111 of the General Laws, the city of
2 Haverhill may be authorized to increase the membership of the board of health from three (3)
3 members to five (5) members. Said members shall be appointed by the mayor with the approval
4 of the city council.
5 SECTION 2. During the month of January, annually following the effective date of this
6 act, the mayor shall appoint one member of the board of health for a term of three years to serve
7 from the first Monday of the following February. The mayor shall appoint a second member of
8 the board of health for a term of two years to serve from the First Monday of the following
9 February. Thereafter, as the terms of the board of health expire, successors shall be appointed for
10 terms of 3 years.
